        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 12:43PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1243 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Louisburg, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Norlina, Middleburg, Drewry, Afton, and Ingleside.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
